  <bioghist id="aspace_4d14772d04bb2c20947be5a09dbd1cfc">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>Willis Grant Johnson was editor of the <title>American Agriculturist</title>.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_0f0142eecb0fedac6fa45bc430990c52">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Correspondence, printed matter, and photographs concerning efforts to obtain funds from the state legislature for the construction of agricultural college buildings at Cornell University. Most of the correspondence is that of Willis Grant Johnson; it indicates Johnson's part in obtaining funding. The principal correspondents are Liberty Hyde Bailey, John Craig, George Malby, Isaac Phillips Roberts, Jacob Gould Schurman, John Spencer, Edwin Stewart, John Lemuel Stone, Henry Hiram Wing, and Daniel Parrish Witter.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_c8c147c0469ce1497907748831055b6e">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Willis Grant Johnson papers, #21-02-471. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
